What type of departmentalization is typical for your company?

44:22.000 --> 44:25.000
Organization structures of companies operating on international markets.

44:27.000 --> 44:30.000
For a similar organization operating on the scale of one country,

44:30.000 --> 44:33.000
companies operating at the international level

44:33.000 --> 44:36.000
should choose an organizational structure

44:36.000 --> 44:39.000
that corresponds to their strategy.

44:39.000 --> 44:42.000
The choice of an organizational structure of such companies

44:42.000 --> 44:45.000
is determined by three main strategic factors.

44:45.000 --> 44:48.000
First, how to encourage the organization

44:48.000 --> 44:51.000
operating mainly within the country

44:51.000 --> 44:54.000
to fully use the opportunities available abroad

44:54.000 --> 44:57.000
for its growth.

44:57.000 --> 45:00.000
Second, how to most effectively use the knowledge of production

45:00.000 --> 45:03.000
and various geographical regions

45:03.000 --> 45:06.000
in order to coordinate business activity

45:07.000 --> 45:10.000
at the international level.

45:10.000 --> 45:13.000
Third, how to coordinate the activities of foreign branches

45:13.000 --> 45:16.000
and branches in many countries,

45:16.000 --> 45:19.000
while preserving their own face.

45:19.000 --> 45:22.000
Since organizational structures of international corporations

45:22.000 --> 45:25.000
are very difficult to analyze,

45:25.000 --> 45:28.000
we will limit ourselves to a brief overview of their basic types.

45:28.000 --> 45:31.000
An entrepreneur who wants to enter the foreign market

45:31.000 --> 45:34.000
with one or several types of new products

45:34.000 --> 45:37.000
usually introduces a position of an export manager,

45:37.000 --> 45:40.000
which is subordinated to the management of the marketing department.

45:40.000 --> 45:43.000
Companies that have significantly increased

45:43.000 --> 45:46.000
the volume of sales on foreign markets

45:46.000 --> 45:49.000
will begin to study the possibility of creating

45:49.000 --> 45:52.000
their own production capacities in the corresponding countries.

45:52.000 --> 45:55.000
However, for foreign sales

45:55.000 --> 45:58.000
in the total volume of the produced product,

45:58.000 --> 46:01.000
the share of these foreign sales

46:01.000 --> 46:04.000
will remain relatively small.

46:04.000 --> 46:07.000
The head of each foreign production branch

46:07.000 --> 46:10.000
is subordinate to the executive director or president of the entire company.

46:10.000 --> 46:13.000
At the same time, the central management of the company

46:13.000 --> 46:16.000
usually provides assistance to its foreign branches

46:16.000 --> 46:19.000
in matters of production,

46:19.000 --> 46:22.000
marketing, financial and human resources.

46:22.000 --> 46:25.000
A certain part of the staff of the company's main management

46:25.000 --> 46:28.000
is transferred to foreign branches

46:28.000 --> 46:31.000
in order to ensure the effective implementation

46:31.000 --> 46:34.000
of strategic plans and tasks of the company as a whole.

46:34.000 --> 46:37.000
As the company's business activity

46:37.000 --> 46:40.000
on the international markets grows,

46:40.000 --> 46:43.000
it usually creates a special international branch.

46:43.000 --> 46:46.000
At the same time, all functions

46:46.000 --> 46:49.000
that ensure the activity of the company on foreign markets

46:49.000 --> 46:52.000
are concentrated in this branch.

46:52.000 --> 46:55.000
The position of the head of such a branch is established,

46:55.000 --> 46:58.000
and it is subordinate to the president of the company.

46:58.000 --> 47:01.000
As a rule, such a head has a fairly wide authority

47:01.000 --> 47:04.000
in all functions and activities of foreign branches.

47:04.000 --> 47:07.000
The divisional structure with the international branch

47:07.000 --> 47:10.000
is presented in the following slide.

47:10.000 --> 47:13.000
Companies that create a divisional structure

47:13.000 --> 47:16.000
with an international branch

47:16.000 --> 47:19.000
have a relatively small volume of foreign sales

47:19.000 --> 47:22.000
compared to sales within the country,

47:22.000 --> 47:25.000
a limited product nomenclature

47:25.000 --> 47:28.000
and a geography of foreign markets.

47:28.000 --> 47:31.000
However, as the volume of foreign sales increases,

47:31.000 --> 47:34.000
the expansion of the assortment of produced products

47:34.000 --> 47:37.000
and the promotion of the company to new economic regions,

47:37.000 --> 47:40.000
the international divisional structure

47:40.000 --> 47:43.000
begins to constrain the company.

47:43.000 --> 47:46.000
At this point, the organizations usually move

47:46.000 --> 47:49.000
to the formation of a global structure.

47:49.000 --> 47:52.000
The global product structure

47:52.000 --> 47:55.000
and the global regional structure

47:55.000 --> 47:58.000
are shown in the following slides.

47:58.000 --> 48:01.000
The global product structure is most suitable

48:01.000 --> 48:04.000
for those companies that have a greater difference

48:04.000 --> 48:07.000
between the types of products produced

48:07.000 --> 48:10.000
than the difference between the regions

48:10.000 --> 48:13.000
in which they are sold.

48:13.000 --> 48:16.000
The difference in production is often due to the fact

48:16.000 --> 48:19.000
that the company produces a wide range of products

48:19.000 --> 48:22.000
that require various technologies.

48:22.000 --> 48:25.000
If the organization is structured

48:25.000 --> 48:28.000
according to the produced product,

48:28.000 --> 48:31.000
it is much easier to achieve the necessary

48:31.000 --> 48:34.000
technological export specializations and coordination.

48:34.000 --> 48:37.000
The geographical regional structure

48:37.000 --> 48:40.000
is more suitable for those

48:40.000 --> 48:43.000
where regional differences are more important

48:43.000 --> 48:46.000
Regional differences are often due to the fact

48:46.000 --> 48:49.000
that various foreign clients of the company

48:49.000 --> 48:52.000
are concentrated in regions with different traditions,

48:52.000 --> 48:55.000
legislation, culture and consumption of products.

48:55.000 --> 48:58.000
As a result, the organization's design

48:58.000 --> 49:01.000
is carried out according to the criteria

49:01.000 --> 49:04.000
of customer demand and marketing methods

49:04.000 --> 49:07.000
in these regions.

