The next topic is

01:04:14.000 --> 01:04:17.000
the modern approaches to building organizational structures

01:04:17.000 --> 01:04:20.000
and situational factors affecting the choice of structure.

01:04:20.000 --> 01:04:23.000
In modern conditions,

01:04:23.000 --> 01:04:26.000
the majority of technical and non-technical tasks

01:04:26.000 --> 01:04:29.000
are based on knowledge.

01:04:29.000 --> 01:04:32.000
Companies no longer need

01:04:32.000 --> 01:04:35.000
numerous unqualified workforce for assembly lines.

01:04:35.000 --> 01:04:38.000
Most of the work requires technical knowledge

01:04:38.000 --> 01:04:41.000
and trained workers.

01:04:41.000 --> 01:04:44.000
Moreover, the smallest number of workers

01:04:44.000 --> 01:04:47.000
is engaged in production of products.

01:04:47.000 --> 01:04:50.000
The majority of employees of the organization

01:04:50.000 --> 01:04:53.000
perform such work as marketing,

01:04:53.000 --> 01:04:56.000
design, technical design,

01:04:56.000 --> 01:04:59.000
technical and economic analysis,

01:04:59.000 --> 01:05:02.000
accounting, management.

01:05:02.000 --> 01:05:05.000
This requires professional experience and knowledge.

01:05:05.000 --> 01:05:08.000
The majority of the work is engaged

01:05:08.000 --> 01:05:11.000
in services in commercial and other organizations.

01:05:11.000 --> 01:05:14.000
According to estimates,

01:05:14.000 --> 01:05:17.000
one third of all jobs are already occupied

01:05:17.000 --> 01:05:20.000
by highly productive teams,

01:05:20.000 --> 01:05:23.000
whose representatives can be called intellectual workers.

01:05:23.000 --> 01:05:26.000
The very nature of intellectual work,

01:05:26.000 --> 01:05:29.000
which includes information gathering,

01:05:29.000 --> 01:05:32.000
creative search, experiments,

01:05:32.000 --> 01:05:35.000
is a key part of intellectual work.

01:05:35.000 --> 01:05:38.000
In certain conditions,

01:05:38.000 --> 01:05:41.000
remote control from the manager

01:05:41.000 --> 01:05:44.000
interferes with work.

01:05:44.000 --> 01:05:47.000
Managers are aimed at performing the work

01:05:47.000 --> 01:05:50.000
if the executors feel that

01:05:50.000 --> 01:05:53.000
their group is being paid attention to.

01:05:53.000 --> 01:05:56.000
The norms of bureaucracy do not imply

01:05:56.000 --> 01:05:59.000
the care for the workers,

01:05:59.000 --> 01:06:02.000
but their complete submission and loyalty to the manager.

01:06:02.000 --> 01:06:05.000
Bureaucracy is too autocratic

01:06:05.000 --> 01:06:08.000
and guided by norms to motivate

01:06:08.000 --> 01:06:11.000
intellectual activity and manage it.

01:06:11.000 --> 01:06:14.000
Creativity and joint work require

01:06:14.000 --> 01:06:17.000
an interested attitude, personal responsibility,

01:06:17.000 --> 01:06:20.000
flexibility in thinking and actions.

01:06:20.000 --> 01:06:23.000
In fact, the so-called norms of bureaucracy

01:06:23.000 --> 01:06:26.000
block innovation and care for people,

01:06:26.000 --> 01:06:29.000
and contradict the meaning of modern activity.

01:06:29.000 --> 01:06:32.000
Many bureaucratic researchers emphasize

01:06:32.000 --> 01:06:35.000
that in a bureaucratic organization

01:06:35.000 --> 01:06:38.000
proper attention is not paid to training workers as an innovation,

01:06:38.000 --> 01:06:41.000
to teamwork and to attention to others.

01:06:41.000 --> 01:06:44.000
For many years, corporations have used

01:06:44.000 --> 01:06:47.000
effective methods of training creativity

01:06:47.000 --> 01:06:50.000
and rationalization thinking,

01:06:50.000 --> 01:06:53.000
but this training was aimed at correcting

01:06:53.000 --> 01:06:56.000
mistakes in education.

01:06:56.000 --> 01:06:59.000
In modern conditions, it is necessary to acquire

01:06:59.000 --> 01:07:02.000
experience of working in a collective,

01:07:02.000 --> 01:07:05.000
to show initiative and responsibility in joint activity,

01:07:05.000 --> 01:07:08.000
to be able to participate in self-management.

01:07:08.000 --> 01:07:11.000
As experience shows,

01:07:11.000 --> 01:07:14.000
bureaucratic systems,

01:07:14.000 --> 01:07:17.000
having pre-implemented the discipline of the team chain,

01:07:17.000 --> 01:07:20.000
do not have enough variety of means

01:07:20.000 --> 01:07:23.000
to solve the existing problems.

01:07:23.000 --> 01:07:26.000
Meanwhile, each active innovation in management

01:07:26.000 --> 01:07:29.000
is based on the strength of the team,

01:07:29.000 --> 01:07:32.000
on inter-functional and inter-linear working groups.

01:07:32.000 --> 01:07:35.000
Organizations become more informed

01:07:35.000 --> 01:07:38.000
when they find an opportunity to use

01:07:38.000 --> 01:07:41.000
a variety of knowledge of each person in the team for common goals.

01:07:41.000 --> 01:07:44.000
With the transition of workers from static work

01:07:44.000 --> 01:07:47.000
to solving a number of problems,

01:07:47.000 --> 01:07:50.000
it becomes necessary to use project management.

01:07:50.000 --> 01:07:53.000
Each project requires, as a rule,

01:07:53.000 --> 01:07:56.000
the creation of interdisciplinary groups.

01:07:56.000 --> 01:07:59.000
Control functions go from the bureaucratic system

01:07:59.000 --> 01:08:02.000
to the project teams.

01:08:02.000 --> 01:08:05.000
Increasing number of works requires

01:08:05.000 --> 01:08:08.000
the unification of knowledge and experience of various specialists.

01:08:08.000 --> 01:08:11.000
Less and less work is done

01:08:11.000 --> 01:08:14.000
within the framework of only one specialization.

01:08:14.000 --> 01:08:17.000
The project worker should be both a narrow specialist

01:08:17.000 --> 01:08:20.000
and have a wider knowledge.

01:08:20.000 --> 01:08:23.000
Rough intervention of the management

01:08:23.000 --> 01:08:26.000
in the activities of the project teams inevitably leads to contradictions,

01:08:26.000 --> 01:08:29.000
to unnecessary difficulties in solving the tasks.

01:08:29.000 --> 01:08:32.000
In an intellectual organization,

01:08:32.000 --> 01:08:35.000
the involvement of workers in the project teams

01:08:35.000 --> 01:08:38.000
allows to promptly identify all the problem nodes.

01:08:38.000 --> 01:08:41.000
At the same time, the mechanism of feedback with the consumers

01:08:42.000 --> 01:08:45.000
is also important.

01:08:45.000 --> 01:08:48.000
In these conditions, the tasks that arise again are solved

01:08:48.000 --> 01:08:51.000
not by increasing the number of workers,

01:08:51.000 --> 01:08:54.000
but on the basis of increasing their qualifications and interoperability,

01:08:54.000 --> 01:08:57.000
strengthening the flexibility of the workforce

01:08:57.000 --> 01:09:00.000
by conducting multifunctional training.

01:09:00.000 --> 01:09:03.000
In order for the organization to become adaptive,

01:09:03.000 --> 01:09:06.000
the preferences of consumers should have a significant influence

01:09:06.000 --> 01:09:09.000
on the activities of the workers.

01:09:09.000 --> 01:09:12.000
The process of transmitting such information through managers is very slow.

01:09:12.000 --> 01:09:15.000
In addition, they may not always know

01:09:15.000 --> 01:09:18.000
the internal needs of the company and the needs of the market.

01:09:18.000 --> 01:09:21.000
If the internal consumer cannot quickly get what is necessary,

01:09:21.000 --> 01:09:24.000
the system cannot operate

01:09:24.000 --> 01:09:27.000
and flexibly serve external consumers.

01:09:27.000 --> 01:09:30.000
The freedom of choice between alternative suppliers

01:09:30.000 --> 01:09:33.000
gives users of internal services the rights

01:09:33.000 --> 01:09:36.000
that external consumers use.

01:09:37.000 --> 01:09:40.000
At the same time, the emphasis shifts from the power of managers

01:09:40.000 --> 01:09:43.000
to the power of consumers.

01:09:43.000 --> 01:09:46.000
In a bureaucratic system,

01:09:46.000 --> 01:09:49.000
the coordination of work with each other at its level

01:09:49.000 --> 01:09:52.000
is not included in the duties of the workers.

01:09:52.000 --> 01:09:55.000
In a post-bureaucratic organization,

01:09:55.000 --> 01:09:58.000
most of the inter-functional connections

01:09:58.000 --> 01:10:01.000
and even many common issues are solved at the level of the working groups.

01:10:01.000 --> 01:10:04.000
Working teams, including workers of all functionalities,

01:10:05.000 --> 01:10:08.000
have the authority to make decisions on all issues.

01:10:08.000 --> 01:10:11.000
Instead of fighting bureaucracy,

01:10:11.000 --> 01:10:14.000
teams work together.

01:10:14.000 --> 01:10:17.000
They study the market,

01:10:17.000 --> 01:10:20.000
determine the value of each product,

01:10:20.000 --> 01:10:23.000
its characteristics,

01:10:23.000 --> 01:10:26.000
appearance and methods of operation.

01:10:26.000 --> 01:10:29.000
The reality has become so complex and multifaceted

01:10:29.000 --> 01:10:32.000
that there is no point in dividing the organization into chains

01:10:33.000 --> 01:10:36.000
where teams will be transferred to solve each emerging problem.

01:10:36.000 --> 01:10:39.000
As a result, integration is achieved

01:10:39.000 --> 01:10:42.000
not hierarchically,

01:10:42.000 --> 01:10:45.000
but at one inter-functional communication level.

01:10:45.000 --> 01:10:48.000
In a modern organization,

01:10:48.000 --> 01:10:51.000
information is transmitted directly without intermediaries.

01:10:51.000 --> 01:10:54.000
Relations of alienation, formality and inequality

01:10:54.000 --> 01:10:57.000
are replaced by relations of openness,

01:10:57.000 --> 01:11:00.000
honesty and relative equality.

01:11:01.000 --> 01:11:04.000
These new realities are designed to completely change the organization.

01:11:04.000 --> 01:11:07.000
The highest point of the listed trends

01:11:07.000 --> 01:11:10.000
is a new type of organization

01:11:10.000 --> 01:11:13.000
called the training organization.

01:11:13.000 --> 01:11:16.000
There is no common opinion

01:11:16.000 --> 01:11:19.000
that what a training organization is.

01:11:19.000 --> 01:11:22.000
Rather, it is an installation or philosophy

01:11:22.000 --> 01:11:25.000
of the organization's most desirable portrait.

01:11:25.000 --> 01:11:28.000
In the following slide,

01:11:29.000 --> 01:11:32.000
the characteristics of two types of organizations

01:11:32.000 --> 01:11:35.000
are compared –

01:11:35.000 --> 01:11:38.000
modern training and traditional vertical.

01:11:38.000 --> 01:11:41.000
In a traditional organization,

01:11:41.000 --> 01:11:44.000
a vertical structure prevails.

01:11:44.000 --> 01:11:47.000
Horizontal coordination is carried out

01:11:47.000 --> 01:11:50.000
by a few special groups,

01:11:50.000 --> 01:11:53.000
teams or project managers.

01:11:53.000 --> 01:11:56.000
Information flows are formalized

01:11:56.000 --> 01:11:59.000
and from bottom to top in the hierarchy of management.

01:11:59.000 --> 01:12:02.000
Information exchange is limited.

01:12:02.000 --> 01:12:05.000
In addition, tasks are divided into narrow,

01:12:05.000 --> 01:12:08.000
specialized tasks of the operation,

01:12:08.000 --> 01:12:11.000
and employees are usually not entitled

01:12:11.000 --> 01:12:14.000
to determine how to perform them.

01:12:14.000 --> 01:12:17.000
The culture is rigid,

01:12:17.000 --> 01:12:20.000
does not encourage risk and change.

01:12:20.000 --> 01:12:23.000
Decisions are made centrally.

01:12:23.000 --> 01:12:26.000
The organization is a place

01:12:26.000 --> 01:12:29.000
where each employee participates

01:12:29.000 --> 01:12:32.000
in the identification and solution of problems,

01:12:32.000 --> 01:12:35.000
which opens up opportunities

01:12:35.000 --> 01:12:38.000
for continuous experiments,

01:12:38.000 --> 01:12:41.000
changes, improvements,

01:12:41.000 --> 01:12:44.000
which develops its ability to grow,

01:12:44.000 --> 01:12:47.000
to learn and to achieve the goal.

01:12:47.000 --> 01:12:50.000
The training organization is characterized

01:12:50.000 --> 01:12:53.000
by the strict adoption of decisions,

01:12:53.000 --> 01:12:56.000
the empowerment of employees

01:12:56.000 --> 01:12:59.000
and a strong adaptive culture.

01:12:59.000 --> 01:13:02.000
In modern training organizations,

01:13:02.000 --> 01:13:05.000
there is no usual vertical structure

01:13:05.000 --> 01:13:08.000
separating the top from the bottom,

01:13:08.000 --> 01:13:11.000
and the units of structural division

01:13:11.000 --> 01:13:14.000
are not functional departments,

01:13:14.000 --> 01:13:17.000
but working streams and core processes.

01:13:17.000 --> 01:13:20.000
The organization is a place

01:13:20.000 --> 01:13:23.000
where employees are trained

01:13:23.000 --> 01:13:26.000
to create new goods or to fulfill orders.

01:13:26.000 --> 01:13:29.000
They work hand in hand,

01:13:29.000 --> 01:13:32.000
which significantly simplifies communication

01:13:32.000 --> 01:13:35.000
and coordination of joint efforts.

01:13:35.000 --> 01:13:38.000
The bricks from which the training organization is made

01:13:38.000 --> 01:13:41.000
are self-managed teams

01:13:41.000 --> 01:13:44.000
including employees of different specialties,

01:13:44.000 --> 01:13:47.000
who directly contact the buyers

01:13:47.000 --> 01:13:50.000
and, if necessary, make adjustments

01:13:50.000 --> 01:13:53.000
to the implementation of the operation and the produced product.

01:13:53.000 --> 01:13:56.000
The team members have the right

01:13:56.000 --> 01:13:59.000
to decide on a wide range of issues

01:13:59.000 --> 01:14:02.000
affecting the organization and production.

01:14:02.000 --> 01:14:05.000
Training, security,

01:14:05.000 --> 01:14:08.000
leave schedule, work methods,

01:14:08.000 --> 01:14:11.000
payment and reward system,

01:14:11.000 --> 01:14:14.000
and the organization's core values

01:14:14.000 --> 01:14:17.000
are not based on strengthening the boundaries

01:14:17.000 --> 01:14:20.000
with other companies,

01:14:20.000 --> 01:14:23.000
but on their elimination.

01:14:23.000 --> 01:14:26.000
Cooperation between organizations

01:14:26.000 --> 01:14:29.000
is provided by combining

01:14:29.000 --> 01:14:32.000
self-managed and virtual teams,

01:14:32.000 --> 01:14:35.000
alliances and partnerships,

01:14:35.000 --> 01:14:38.000
virtual organizations and other structural innovations.

01:14:38.000 --> 01:14:41.000
To be able to identify the needs

01:14:41.000 --> 01:14:44.000
and solve the problems,

01:14:44.000 --> 01:14:47.000
employees must be able to orient themselves

01:14:47.000 --> 01:14:50.000
in what is happening around them,

01:14:50.000 --> 01:14:53.000
understand the organization's overall activity

01:14:53.000 --> 01:14:56.000
and also realize their place in it.

01:14:56.000 --> 01:14:59.000
Therefore, each of them needs access

01:14:59.000 --> 01:15:02.000
to data such as budgets,

01:15:02.000 --> 01:15:05.000
department expenses, revenue indicators.

01:15:05.000 --> 01:15:08.000
Electronic communication is one of the most important aspects

01:15:08.000 --> 01:15:11.000
of information exchange and knowledge.

01:15:11.000 --> 01:15:14.000
Computer networks, Internet technologies,

01:15:14.000 --> 01:15:17.000
intranets and extranets

01:15:17.000 --> 01:15:20.000
all contribute to redistributing knowledge,

01:15:20.000 --> 01:15:23.000
to presenting information to those

01:15:23.000 --> 01:15:26.000
who really need it,

01:15:26.000 --> 01:15:29.000
to the constant contact between employees.

01:15:29.000 --> 01:15:32.000
However, a great deal of importance

01:15:32.000 --> 01:15:35.000
is given to personal communication

01:15:35.000 --> 01:15:38.000
and, above all, to the ability to listen to each other.

01:15:38.000 --> 01:15:41.000
In traditional organizations,

01:15:41.000 --> 01:15:44.000
decisions are passed up in a hierarchy for approval.

01:15:44.000 --> 01:15:47.000
The right and responsibility of making decisions

01:15:47.000 --> 01:15:50.000
lies with those who are closest to the problem.

01:15:50.000 --> 01:15:53.000
In traditional vertical organizations,

01:15:53.000 --> 01:15:56.000
top managers are responsible

01:15:56.000 --> 01:15:59.000
for the development of the strategy,

01:15:59.000 --> 01:16:02.000
and those who have the necessary knowledge and experience

01:16:02.000 --> 01:16:05.000
to manage the company.

01:16:05.000 --> 01:16:08.000
The leaders of the learning organization

01:16:08.000 --> 01:16:11.000
also influence the vision, direction and formulation of the strategy,

01:16:11.000 --> 01:16:14.000
but not only them.

01:16:14.000 --> 01:16:17.000
Everyone participates in the strategic process.

01:16:17.000 --> 01:16:20.000
Information is collected by those

01:16:20.000 --> 01:16:23.000
who directly contact buyers, suppliers,

01:16:23.000 --> 01:16:26.000
other organizations.

01:16:26.000 --> 01:16:29.000
It is they who recognize changes,

01:16:29.000 --> 01:16:32.000
identify needs and find solutions,

01:16:32.000 --> 01:16:35.000
and then offer their ideas

01:16:35.000 --> 01:16:38.000
to other members of the organization for discussion.

01:16:38.000 --> 01:16:41.000
Another forming strategy of the learning organization

01:16:41.000 --> 01:16:44.000
can be partnership relations

01:16:44.000 --> 01:16:47.000
with suppliers, buyers and even competitors.

01:16:47.000 --> 01:16:50.000
With other companies,

01:16:50.000 --> 01:16:53.000
the learning organization sets relatively permeable boundaries,

01:16:54.000 --> 01:16:57.000
which opens access to information

01:16:57.000 --> 01:17:00.000
about new strategic needs and directions.

01:17:00.000 --> 01:17:03.000
Instead of keeping a distance

01:17:03.000 --> 01:17:06.000
from buyers and suppliers,

01:17:06.000 --> 01:17:09.000
the modern learning organization

01:17:09.000 --> 01:17:12.000
brings them into the ranks of partners,

01:17:12.000 --> 01:17:15.000
whose efforts are aimed at achieving common goals.

01:17:15.000 --> 01:17:18.000
The employees of the learning organization

01:17:18.000 --> 01:17:21.000
are endowed with extraordinary powers,

01:17:21.000 --> 01:17:24.000
in particular, with the right and even the duty

01:17:24.000 --> 01:17:27.000
to choose the ways to achieve the goals set before them.

01:17:27.000 --> 01:17:30.000
Endowment with power or delegating

01:17:30.000 --> 01:17:33.000
means that the employees are guaranteed

01:17:33.000 --> 01:17:36.000
the obtaining of the necessary decisions

01:17:36.000 --> 01:17:39.000
and effective activity, freedom,

01:17:39.000 --> 01:17:42.000
knowledge and skills.

01:17:42.000 --> 01:17:45.000
Instead of a forcible division of the labor process

01:17:45.000 --> 01:17:48.000
into strictly defined, narrowly specialized tasks and operations,

01:17:49.000 --> 01:17:52.000
the leaders of the learning organization

01:17:52.000 --> 01:17:55.000
sanction the independent conduct of the employees of the correctional services

01:17:55.000 --> 01:17:58.000
in accordance with the development of the situation.

01:17:58.000 --> 01:18:01.000
The number of rules and procedures is reduced to a minimum,

01:18:01.000 --> 01:18:04.000
and the right to manage work tasks

01:18:04.000 --> 01:18:07.000
is assigned to those who directly perform them.

01:18:09.000 --> 01:18:12.000
Corporate culture is a combination of common

01:18:12.000 --> 01:18:15.000
key values, beliefs, knowledge and knowledge.

01:18:18.000 --> 01:18:21.000
It is the basis of the learning organization.

01:18:21.000 --> 01:18:24.000
Corporate culture of the learning organization

01:18:24.000 --> 01:18:27.000
encourages openness,

01:18:27.000 --> 01:18:30.000
lack of barriers, equality,

01:18:30.000 --> 01:18:33.000
continuous improvement and change.

01:18:33.000 --> 01:18:36.000
Such an organization always moves forward.

01:18:36.000 --> 01:18:39.000
Of course, there are no perfect learning organizations,

01:18:39.000 --> 01:18:42.000
but get acquainted at least with the experience of the company

01:18:42.000 --> 01:18:45.000
Sheprell Steel and in the course of the implementation

