of the learning organization.

01:19:04.000 --> 01:19:07.000
What structure should be preferred?

01:19:07.000 --> 01:19:10.000
Formal vertical hierarchy

01:19:10.000 --> 01:19:13.000
or the one that promotes horizontal coordination and cooperation?

01:19:14.000 --> 01:19:17.000
The answer depends on the specific circumstances

01:19:17.000 --> 01:19:20.000
in which the company operates

01:19:20.000 --> 01:19:23.000
or the situational factors affecting the organizational structure.

01:19:23.000 --> 01:19:26.000
Organizational structure studies show

01:19:26.000 --> 01:19:29.000
that the choice of a rigid or flexible structure

01:19:29.000 --> 01:19:32.000
is determined by such factors as

01:19:32.000 --> 01:19:35.000
strategy, external environment,

01:19:35.000 --> 01:19:38.000
production technology and interdependence between departments.

01:19:38.000 --> 01:19:41.000
The correct structure is the one

01:19:41.000 --> 01:19:44.000
that is most suitable for situational factors.

01:19:44.000 --> 01:19:47.000
Below we will consider the influence of each of the four factors

01:19:47.000 --> 01:19:50.000
on the organizational structure.

01:19:50.000 --> 01:19:53.000
Research on the formation of organizational structures

01:19:53.000 --> 01:19:56.000
conducted by Chandler on the example of the activities

01:19:56.000 --> 01:19:59.000
of the 80 largest companies in the United States

01:19:59.000 --> 01:20:02.000
shows that the strategy has a determining effect on the structure.

01:20:02.000 --> 01:20:05.000
Changes in the structure follow changes in the strategy.

01:20:05.000 --> 01:20:08.000
He found that if the organization is not able to

01:20:08.000 --> 01:20:11.000
follow the changes in the strategy,

01:20:11.000 --> 01:20:14.000
the results are not effective.

01:20:14.000 --> 01:20:17.000
Since the pace of change in the external environment is increasing,

01:20:17.000 --> 01:20:20.000
the enterprise should clarify its strategies more often

01:20:20.000 --> 01:20:23.000
than it was in the past

01:20:23.000 --> 01:20:26.000
to establish their compliance with market requirements.

01:20:26.000 --> 01:20:29.000
This means that changes in the strategy

01:20:29.000 --> 01:20:32.000
precede changes in the structure and lead to them.

01:20:32.000 --> 01:20:35.000
The change in the structure is not a result of the organization's actions

01:20:35.000 --> 01:20:38.000
but a result of the changes in the structure and lead to them.

01:20:38.000 --> 01:20:41.000
The management structure is more inertial in relation to the strategy

01:20:41.000 --> 01:20:44.000
because the factors that affect the choice of the structure

01:20:44.000 --> 01:20:47.000
change slower in time

01:20:47.000 --> 01:20:50.000
than those that affect the choice of the strategy.

