The slide shows a simplified continuum

01:20:53.000 --> 01:20:56.000
illustrating the interconnection of structural approaches

01:20:56.000 --> 01:20:59.000
and strategic goals.

01:20:59.000 --> 01:21:02.000
A pure functional structure

01:21:03.000 --> 01:21:06.000
is the most adequate organization

01:21:06.000 --> 01:21:09.000
focused on improving internal efficiency

01:21:09.000 --> 01:21:12.000
by using resources

01:21:12.000 --> 01:21:15.000
but it is not able to provide flexibility or innovation.

01:21:15.000 --> 01:21:18.000
On the contrary, a team structure

01:21:18.000 --> 01:21:21.000
is recommended by the organization

01:21:21.000 --> 01:21:24.000
whose goal is to increase the degree of flexibility

01:21:24.000 --> 01:21:27.000
and accelerate innovation processes.

01:21:27.000 --> 01:21:30.000
A team structure facilitates the process of building

01:21:31.000 --> 01:21:34.000
reorganization changes and a temporary response

01:21:34.000 --> 01:21:37.000
to changes occurring in the external environment

01:21:37.000 --> 01:21:40.000
but at the expense of less productive use of resources.

01:21:40.000 --> 01:21:43.000
The compliance of the environment and structure

01:21:43.000 --> 01:21:46.000
is also a necessary condition for the effectiveness

01:21:46.000 --> 01:21:49.000
of organizational activity.

01:21:49.000 --> 01:21:52.000
The situational interconnections between external uncertainty

01:21:52.000 --> 01:21:55.000
and the structural approach are reflected in the following slide.

01:21:55.000 --> 01:21:58.000
The relatively stable external environment

01:21:59.000 --> 01:22:02.000
is the most adequate traditional organizational structure

01:22:02.000 --> 01:22:05.000
with emphasis on vertical management.

01:22:05.000 --> 01:22:08.000
In these circumstances,

01:22:08.000 --> 01:22:11.000
there is practically no need for changes

01:22:11.000 --> 01:22:14.000
more close coordination or increase in flexibility.

01:22:14.000 --> 01:22:17.000
The emphasis can be placed on specialization

01:22:17.000 --> 01:22:20.000
centralized decision-making and wide-scale control.

01:22:20.000 --> 01:22:23.000
If the variability of the external environment is relatively large

01:22:23.000 --> 01:22:26.000
the horizontal structure is more preferable.

01:22:27.000 --> 01:22:30.000
The structure should also correspond to the production technology.

01:22:30.000 --> 01:22:33.000
The technology includes knowledge,

01:22:33.000 --> 01:22:36.000
tools of labor, methods and types of activities

01:22:36.000 --> 01:22:39.000
aimed at transforming the incoming resources

01:22:39.000 --> 01:22:42.000
of the organization into ready-made products.

01:22:42.000 --> 01:22:45.000
Equipment, staff qualification

01:22:45.000 --> 01:22:48.000
and work ethics are also related to technology.

01:22:48.000 --> 01:22:51.000
The organization should be able to perform

01:22:51.000 --> 01:22:54.000
its tasks in a more efficient and efficient way.

